check_description: Validates the video quality by checking Bits Per Pixel Per Frame (BPPF). Ensures the video is not overly compressed or has quality issues.
The recorded video has frame drops. Please ensure you are using a system with a minimum of 8GB RAM and processor at least i5/Ryzen 5 in Windows/Linux or any Macbook
Checks if the events.jsonl file exists, which contains the activity log of user interactions during the recording.
Verifies that the events.jsonl file has content (greater than 10 bytes).
Verifies that the extracted folder name matches the task slug. The ZIP file should contain a single folder with the same name as the task.
Verifies that the video FPS after processing equals the expected threshold (30 fps).
Detects idle periods exceeding threshold (25 seconds).
Checks if the metadata.json file exists, which contains recording information and configuration.
Verifies that the metadata.json file has content (greater than 10 bytes).
Detects keypresses of non-relevant or unusual keys that should not appear in normal usage.
Detects if a paste action (Ctrl+V/Cmd+V) occurs before any copy action (Ctrl+C/Cmd+C), indicating pre-copied content.
Verifies that the Taggr app version in metadata.json is >= 1.4.5. Please update your Taggr app if this check fails.
Ensures the recording is in the correct task folder with the expected task slug name.
Verifies that exactly one video file exists. Multiple or no video files will fail this check.
Checks if a video file exists in the recording folder. At least one video file is required.
Ensures the video file has a reasonable size (greater than 10 bytes).
Validates system configuration metrics: cursor matching, frame gap detection, and keypress verification.
